<p>I have a for loop, and I initialise the variables inside that loop. After it, I need to manipulate that variables, but the compiler says that <em>variables are not initialised</em>. </p>  <pre><code>public class Solution {     static void displayPathtoPrincess(int n, String[] grid) {         String[][] visual = new String[n][n];         for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {             char[] myGrid = grid[i].toCharArray();             for (int j = 0; j &lt; n; j++) {                 visual[i][j] = myGrid[j] + "";             }         }          int pX;         int pY;         int bX;         int bY;         // rescue the princess         for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {             for (int j = 0; j &lt; n; j++) {                 if (visual[i][j].equals("p")) {                     pX = j;                     pY = i;                 }                 if (visual[i][j].equals("m")) {                     bX = j;                     bY = i;                 }             }         }         System.out.println(pY + "");         System.out.println(pX + "");     }      public static void main(String[] args) {         Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);         int m;         m = in.nextInt();         String grid[] = new String[m];         for (int i = 0; i &lt; m; i++) {             grid[i] = in.next();         }          displayPathtoPrincess(m, grid);     } } </code></pre>  <p><code>if</code> condition is <code>true</code> at some point. In fact if I move the print statements inside the <code>if</code> it works.<br> How can solve this problem?</p>